    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Anyone has any insights on how to keep user connected to same node behind the load balancer? I'm all ears. This may also be resolved when we make some improvements to the backend / caching mechanism.\r\n\r\nThis is happening a lot lately (meaning since thanksgiving) due to \r\n\r\n1. super full tx pools \r\n2. hitting different nodes which may not have received the latest tx yet \r\n3. being 100% on parity ATM which handles grabbing transaction count (the nonce) a bit differently than geth\r\n\r\n@skubakdj can probably provide more insights, but ideally the user would never have to refresh the nonce so there wouldn't have to be a button. ðŸ˜Š",
