    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't know of a way to ensure that a request is routed to a specific node behind the load-balancer, but that's certainly an interesting concept. Perhaps by forking the node and having some customID that the client then uses to make subsequent requests with. The load-balancer would also have to be configured to allow this. Not sure how this would be implemented in practice.\r\n\r\nEven in the case where the node returns the \"correct\" nonce after the user decrypts their wallet, they may have sent a tx from another wallet using the same private key. Unless we have a websocket that will push the updated nonce, or we poll, the user wouldn't be able to have their nonce automatically updated (without taking action to refresh themselves).\r\n\r\n ",
